  "local_port": 37666,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some best resume?",
  "response": "Creating a standout resume requires attention to detail and a strategic approach to showcasing your skills, experiences, and achievements. Here are some tips for crafting a strong resume:\n\n1. **Clear Structure and Layout**:\n   - Use a clean, professional format.\n   - Include sections such as Contact Information, Summary, Work Experience, Education, Skills, and Certifications.\n\n2. **Professional Summary**:\n   - Write a brief summary at the beginning that highlights your key qualifications and career goals.\n   - Make it specific to the job you're applying for.\n\n3. **Tailored Content**:\n   - Customize your resume for each job application.\n   - Highlight relevant experience and skills that match the job description.\n\n4. **Achievements and Metrics**:\n   - Emphasize accomplishments rather than just duties.\n   - Use quantifiable metrics (e.g., \"increased sales by 20%\").\n\n5. **Keywords**:\n   - Include industry-specific keywords that align with the job posting.\n   - This helps with applicant tracking systems (ATS).\n\n6. **Skills**:\n   - List relevant hard and soft skills.\n   - Consider a mix of technical skills and interpersonal skills.\n\n7. **Education and Certifications**:\n   - Include your educational background and any relevant certifications.\n   - Mention honors or distinctions if applicable.\n\n8. **Professional Experience**:\n   - Detail your work history in reverse chronological order.\n   - Include job titles, company names, locations, and dates of employment.\n   - Describe your responsibilities and achievements clearly.\n\n9. **Formatting**:\n   - Use bullet points for easy readability.\n   - Ensure consistent font and formatting throughout the document.\n   - Keep it to one or two pages, depending on your experience level.\n\n10. **Proofreading**:\n    - Check for spelling and grammatical errors.\n    - Ensure all information is accurate and up-to-date.\n\n**Sample Resume Outline**:\n\n**Contact Information**\n- Name\n- Address\n- Phone Number\n- Email Address\n- LinkedIn Profile (optional)\n\n**Professional Summary**\n[Brief summary of your career and key qualifications]\n\n**Work Experience**\n[Job Title] | [Company Name] | [Location] | [Dates of Employment]\n- [Key responsibility or achievement]\n- [Key responsibility or achievement]\n- [Key responsibility or achievement]\n\n[Job Title] | [Company Name] | [Location] | [Dates of Employment]\n- [Key responsibility or achievement]\n- [Key responsibility or achievement]\n- [Key responsibility or achievement]\n\n**Education**\n[Degree] | [School Name] | [Location] | [Graduation Year]\n- [Relevant coursework or honors]\n\n**Skills**\n- [Skill 1]\n- [Skill 2]\n- [Skill 3]\n- [Skill 4]\n\n**Certifications**\n- [Certification Name] | [Issuing Organization] | [Date]\n\nBy following these guidelines and tailoring your resume to each job opportunity, you can create a compelling resume that effectively showcases your qualifications to potential employers.",
